RACE.RACE_TEXT: FAIR GROUNDS RACE 1 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 43. Maiden Claiming Purse 15000. FOR ACCREDITED LA BRED MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 117 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HIGHLY WICKED set the pace two wide into the first turn, cleared and crossed over approaching the backstretch, drew away from a pair of outer chasers with nine sixteenths to go, opened up around the far turn, widened under driving pressure through upper stretch, and was put to wraps at the sixteenth pole. PICKIN ANA GRINNIN broke on top, yet inwardly causing her to shy and nimbly avoid the inner rail, raced off of the pace along the inside, pulled in the two path to be rank behind foes around the first turn, shifted out down the backstretch, claimed place from a pair of inner foes at the three furlong pole, and pulled clear of the rest while no match for the winner. REINA ACES popped open the gate without leaving it pre-race, pursued from midpack along the inside, chased in the four path around the far turn, tucked to the two path while tiring entering the lane, yet improved between horses in midstretch for a minor share. BLESS D'SOUTH broke a step slow, trailed in the four path around the first turn, fanned to the six path in upper stretch, and moved up. MIDNIGHT FLAME broke a beat slow, pressed three wide leaving the first turn, but failed to keep pace with the leader at the nine sixteenths pole, and tired around the far turn. TAZZHER bumped with an inner rival at the start, and was outrun in the four to three paths. ZIPPING MOLLY prompted the pace inside of a rival into the first turn, switched course outside of that foe around that bend as another out rival moved to apply pressure, but failed to keep pace with the leader with nine sixteenths to go, and faded around the far turn. SANGIOVESE bumped with an outer rival at the start, chased two wide, but was done entering the far turn.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SPECIAL OPERATOR was off a step slow was able to find his stride in the five path down the backside, gained ground in the turn as he circled the field from the outside, continued to gain momentum in the stretch, caught the early leader near the furlong ground, those two matched strides late, battled grudgingly, and prevailed. MONGOLIAN BEE was fast out of the gates, set the early pace, was caught by the eventual winner late in the stretch, battled for the win but didn't have enough toady. GALLANT BUCK settled behind the early leaders in the second tier, waited for room into the turn, was brought out five wide into and down the stretch had a late kick but it wasn't enough to catch the winner. BACK BEAT was pushed out early by another rival, settled down the back side four wide, stayed wide through out the rest of the race, was driven down the stretch and made up ground with a late game effort but had to settled for fourth. BELLO CREEDO vied for the lead, was rated just off the leaders hip, was collared by the eventual winner in the turn and tired in the stretch. MIDNIGHT DREAMING was never involved.

CHARRIERE prompted the pace inside of the leader, attempted to switch outside of that foe coming to the five furlong pole, but allowed for the eventual winner to move through in the process, tucked and chased that foe from the rail around the far turn, then weakened between horses in upper stretch. OATH OF ALLEGIANCE set the pace two wide, tossed his head from restraint entering the backstretch, got headed by a rail bidder approaching the nine sixteenths pole, and wilted between horses around the far turn.
